- "Public attention" is measured by the average pageviews of the figure's biography, with a threshold of more than 1000 views;
- "Significance score" is a measure of the historical importance of the figure, with higher scores indicating greater significance.

- "more prominent figures" refers to historical figures with a score greater than 0.5;
- The score represents the historical significance of the figure;
- The field of influence includes areas such as politics, science, etc.

